article.headline: Buckeyes use two big runs to put game away
article.story:
COLUMBUS, Ohio (AP) -- Jessica Davenport had 18 points and nine rebounds to lead Ohio State to an 80-43 win over Yale on Saturday.

Caity Matter finished with nine points and four assists, Tamarah Riley added 12 points and Brandie Hoskins scored 11 for the Buckeyes (4-1).

Erica Davis led Yale (0-3) with 14 points.

Davenport scored seven points in a 16-4 run that gave Ohio State (No. 10 ESPN/USA Today, No. 11 AP) a 24-10 lead with 9:47 left in the first half.

The Buckeyes led 39-21 at the break and went on a 20-2 run at the start of the second half, extending their lead to 59-23 with 12:52 left. Michelle Munoz scored eight of her 10 points in the run.

Ohio State outscored Yale 48-26 in the paint and shot 56 percent. Yale shot 36 percent.
